## OER Compliance

{% raw %}    {{2}}{% endraw %}
**Only {{ stats.oer_compliant_percent }}%** of courses use OER-compliant licenses!

{% raw %}    {{3}}{% endraw %}
Without explicit open licenses, materials are technically "all rights reserved" under copyright law—preventing the **5R activities**:

- **Retain** – keep a copy
- **Reuse** – use in various ways
- **Revise** – adapt and modify
- **Remix** – combine with other content
- **Redistribute** – share with others

---

## Why This Matters

{% raw %}    {{5}}{% endraw %}
Educators cannot legally reuse "public" materials without explicit permission.

{% raw %}    {{6}}{% endraw %}
**The contrast:**

| Platform | Licensing Culture |
|----------|-------------------|
| Open Source Software | Licensing is standard |
| LiaScript OER | Licensing often forgotten |

---

## Recommendations

{% raw %}    {{7}}{% endraw %}
**For course authors:**
- Add explicit licenses (CC-BY or CC-BY-SA recommended)
- Use LiaScript's `content_license` header field

{% raw %}    {{8}}{% endraw %}
**For the LiaScript community:**
- Include license selection in starter templates
- Promote licensing awareness

